ELSE IF STATEMENTS IN JAVASCRIPT

Else if statements/conditions are statements that are normally used when the 
previous statement/condition used is false. An if statement/condition must first 
occur before the else if statement/condition are used.

N0T RECOMMENDED
else if (true) {
	console.log('You are a developer');
} 

This is not recommended because it didnt start with an if statement/condition.

RECOMMENDED
if (false) {
	console.log('You are not a developer');
} else if (true) {
	console.log('You are a developer');
}

This is recommended because it starts with an if statement/condition